sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Return the first User ID found based on the following search criteria.

Inputs:

  • First Name
  • Last Name
  • Display Name - Name displayed in the address book for the user.
  • User Login ID - Login User ID is same as User Principal Name(UPN). Example: johndoe@snc.com.
  • Email Alias - Alias configured for an email account. A single email account can have more than one alias.

At least one input is required. Using multiple inputs will help to narrow down the search.

Outputs:

  • Status - Will be set to “User Found" if a single user is found, "User Not Found" if no user is found, "Multiple Users Found" if multiple users are found matching the search criteria, or “Error" if a failure in Azure AD occurs.
  • User ID - First user found with matching criteria in Azure AD.
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

The status will be Error only in case of any failure in Azure AD.

Error Messages:

  • Something went wrong. Response was empty
  • Unauthorized
  • Set at least one of the properties - First Name/Last Name/Display Name/User Login ID/E-Mail Alias
  • Insufficient Permissions. Please Check OAuth Token and scope permission
  • Forbidden Request. Please Check OAuth Token and scope permission
  • Invalid Connection
  • Unknown Error

To use this action, a corresponding Azure AD connection and credential must be created and associated with the Azure AD Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More
